properties.name: Contents
properties.description: The set of contents associated with this item.

properties.name: ContentType

properties.name: CreationDate
properties.description: The date and time when this item was created.

properties.name: CreatorEntityKey
properties.description: The ID of the creator of this catalog item.

properties.name: Description
properties.description: A dictionary of localized descriptions. Key is language code and localized string is the value. The neutral locale is required.

properties.name: DisplayProperties
properties.description: Game specific properties for display purposes. This is an arbitrary JSON blob.

properties.name: ETag
properties.description: The current ETag value that can be used for optimistic concurrency in the If-None-Match header.

properties.name: Id
properties.description: The unique ID of the catalog item.

properties.name: Images
properties.description: The images associated with this item. Images can be thumbnails or screenshots.

properties.name: IsHidden
properties.description: Indicates if the item is hidden

properties.name: LastModifiedDate
properties.description: The date and time this item was last updated.

properties.name: Platforms
properties.description: The platforms supported by this item.

properties.name: StartDate
properties.description: The date of when the item will be available. If not provided then the product will appear immediately.

properties.name: Tags
properties.description: The list of tags that are associated with this item.

properties.name: Title
properties.description: A dictionary of localized titles. Key is language code and localized string is the value. The neutral locale is required.

CatalogSearchRequest.name: CatalogSearchRequest
CatalogSearchRequest.description:
Only community items that have been published with the Publish Item API will be
                returned by Search even for the creator. The creator should use the List Items API to
                view all of their own items.

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: Filter
properties.description: An OData filter used to refine the search query.

properties.name: OrderBy
properties.description: An OData orderBy used to order the results of the search query.

properties.name: Search
properties.description: The text to search for.

properties.name: Select
properties.description: An OData select query option used to augment the search results. If not defined, the default search result metadata will be returned.

properties.name: Skip
properties.description: The number of results to skip.

properties.name: TitleId
properties.description: The ID of the title that this catalog item is associated with.

properties.name: Top
properties.description: The number of results to retrieve.

properties.name: Count
properties.description: The total count of hits for the search query.

properties.name: Items
properties.description: The paginated set of results for the search query.

properties.name: MaxClientVersion
properties.description: The maximum client version that this content is compatible with.

properties.name: MinClientVersion
properties.description: The minimum client version that this content is compatible with.

properties.name: Tags
properties.description: The list of tags that are associated with this content.

properties.name: Type
properties.description: The client-defined type of the content.

properties.name: Url
properties.description: The Azure CDN URL for retrieval of the catalog item binary content.

CreateUploadUrlsRequest.name: CreateUploadUrlsRequest
CreateUploadUrlsRequest.description:
Upload URLs point to Azure Blobs; clients must follow the Microsoft Azure Storage Blob Service REST
                API pattern for uploading content. The response contains upload URLs and IDs for each file. The IDs and URLs
                returned must be added to the item metadata and commited using the CreateDraftItem or UpdateDraftItem Item APIs.

PublishItemRequest.name: PublishItemRequest
PublishItemRequest.description:
The call kicks off a workflow to publish the item to the public catalog.
                The Publish Status API should be used to monitor the publish job.

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: ETag
properties.description: ETag of the catalog item to published from the working catalog to the public catalog. Used for optimistic concurrency. If the provided ETag does not match the ETag in the current working catalog, the request will be reject. If not provided, the current version of the document in the working catalog will be published.

properties.name: ItemId
properties.description: ID of the catalog item to publish from the working catalog to the public catalog.

calls.name: CreateDraftItem
calls.summary: Creates a new community catalog item in the working catalog using provided metadata.
calls.requestDetails: The item will not be published to the public catalog until the user makes a call to the PublishItem API.

calls.name: CreateUploadUrls
calls.summary: Creates one or more upload URLs which can be used by the client to upload raw mod file data.
calls.requestDetails: Upload URLs point to Azure Blobs; clients must follow the Microsoft Azure Storage Blob Service REST API pattern for uploading content. The response contains upload URLs and IDs for each file. The IDs and URLs returned must be added to the item metadata and commited using the CreateDraftItem or UpdateDraftItem Item APIs.

calls.name: DeleteItem
calls.summary: Removes an item from working catalog and all published versions from the public catalog.

calls.name: GetConfig
calls.summary: Gets the configuration for the user generated content catalog.

calls.name: GetDraftItem
calls.summary: Retrieves an item from the working catalog. This item represents the current working state of the community item.

calls.name: GetDraftItems
calls.summary: Retrieves a paginated list of the items created by a user.

calls.name: GetPublishedItem
calls.summary: Retrieves an item from the public catalog.

calls.name: GetPublishStatus
calls.summary: Gets the status of a publish of an item.

calls.name: PublishItem
calls.summary: Initiates a publish of a item from the working catalog to the public catalog.
calls.requestDetails: The call kicks off a workflow to publish the item to the public catalog. The Publish Status API should be used to monitor the publish job.

calls.name: Search
calls.summary: Execute a search against the public catalog using the provided search parameters and returns a set of paginated results.
calls.requestDetails: Only community items that have been published with the Publish Item API will be returned by Search even for the creator. The creator should use the List Items API to view all of their own items.

calls.name: SetConfig
calls.summary: Gets the configuration for the user generated content catalog.

calls.name: UpdateDraftItem
calls.summary: Update the metadata for an item in the working catalog.
